The paper deals with testing the identity and closeness of discrete distributions while ensuring differential privacy. This involves techniques from data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
